data.title: Carlos Boozer, Basketball Player
data.meta_description: Carlos Boozer stats and bio. Stats averages season by season. Quick access to game by game stats.
data.text:
Carlos Boozer - Points

Carlos Boozer scores a career high 41 points (2007)

On March 26, 2007, Carlos Boozer tied his career high in points in a NBA game. That day he scored 41 points in Utah's home win against Washington, 103-97. He also had 16 rebounds, 2 assists. He shot 15/21 from two, shooting at 71.4% from the field. He also shot 11/14 from the free-throw line.

Carlos Boozer - Rebounds

Carlos Boozer grabs a career high 23 rebounds (2010)

On February 21, 2010, Carlos Boozer set his career high in rebounds in a NBA game. That day he grabbed 23 rebounds in Utah's road win against Portland, 89-93. He also had 22 points, 5 assists and 1 block.

Carlos Boozer - Assists

Carlos Boozer gives a career high 10 assists (2008)

On February 13, 2008, Carlos Boozer set his career high in assists in a NBA game. That day he dished 10 assists in Utah's road win against Seattle, 93-112. He also had 22 points, 11 rebounds, 5 steals.

Carlos Boozer - Steals

Carlos Boozer has a career high 5 steals (2004)

On March 16, 2004, Carlos Boozer tied his career high in steals in a NBA game. That day he reached 5 steals in Cleveland's home win against Chicago, 111-87. He also had 22 points, 13 rebounds and 3 assists.

Carlos Boozer - Blocks

Carlos Boozer blocks a career high 4 shots (2003)

On October 29, 2003, Carlos Boozer set his career high in blocks in a NBA game. That day he went for 4 blocks in Cleveland's road loss against Sacramento, 106-92. He also had 14 points, 11 rebounds and 3 assists.
